My suggestion is to use a Model that converts any non-numeric value to a empty string and use this model in your form:

     Ext.define(&#39;Fiddle.model.ageModel&#39;, {
                extend: &#39;Ext.data.Model&#39;,
                requires: [
                    &#39;Ext.data.field.Field&#39;
                ],
                fields: [{
                    name: &#39;name&#39;
                }, {
                    name: &#39;age&#39;,
                    convert: function (v, rec) {
                        return typeof (v) === &#39;number&#39; ? v : &#39;&#39;;
                    },
    
                }]
            });

See this &lt;a href=&quot;https://fiddle.sencha.com/#view/editor&amp;fiddle/2vlb&quot;&gt;exemple&lt;/a&gt;

I prefer to use [`Number`][1] field in model with [`allowNull`][2] variable.

And `allowBlank` must be true in `numberfield`.

Ex. 
```javascript
Ext.define(&#39;Person&#39;, {
    extend: &#39;Ext.data.Model&#39;,
    fields: [
        { name: &#39;age&#39;, type: &#39;number&#39;, allowNull: true }
    ]
});
```


  [1]: https://docs.sencha.com/extjs/6.7.0/classic/Ext.data.field.Number.html
  [2]: https://docs.sencha.com/extjs/6.7.0/classic/Ext.data.field.Number.html#cfg-allowNull

